OL,3,CMPs 'flabbergasted' as gambling boss
OL,4,Cdenies industry causes social harm
OL,6,FOn four occasions, Hurst denied that
OL,7,Fgambling creates "social harm" - while
OL,8,Facknowledging a minority of people do
OL,9,Fsuffer harm through gambling.
OL,11,F"I think there are people who will
OL,12,Fhave problems with their gambling, but
OL,13,Fthat is 0.4% of the population," she
OL,14,Ftold MPs. "But I don't think it's
OL,15,Fright to categorise the gambling
OL,16,Findustry as creating social harms."
OL,18,FHurst also argued that online gambling
OL,19,Fwas no more addictive than betting on
OL,20,Fhorse racing - a claim campaigners
OL,21,Fstrongly dispute.
